        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurens, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laurens.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
